gomodel:SYNGO_180  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Immunostaining in Calyx in wistar Rats.\n\n22/1/2017 Pim:\n-Fig.5 bargraph: synaptophysin-colocalized Kv signal is regarded as presynaptic localization. The remaining signal (exlcluding the nucleus) is caused by Kv localized to the soma of MNTB cells; for the calyx of held these are considered to represent postsynaptic Kv channels. [see: http://www.nature.com/neuro/journal/v8/n4/images/nn0405-402-F1.gif]\n-\"Intrinsic component ...\" element derived from the TM domains of the Kv channel subunit.. Experimental description: MM: Immunocytochemistry. Wistar rats (13-15 d old) were anesthetized with Nembutal and transcardially perfused with a fixative (4% parafor- maldehyde and 0.1% picric acid in 0.1 M sodium phosphate, pH 7.4). After fixation, rats were decapitated, and tissue blocks of the brainstem including the MNTB region were removed for postfixation for 1 d at 4°C" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_180" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

